Document: EditorExportPlatformLinuxBSD
Path: godot/classes/class_editorexportplatformlinuxbsd.rst
Summary: Defines export settings for Linux/BSD platforms.

EditorExportPlatformLinuxBSD

Inherits: EditorExportPlatform < RefCounted

This class handles the export of projects to Linux and BSD platforms. It provides specific options and configurations tailored for these operating systems.

Properties:
* export_compressor (String, Default: "zstd"): The compression method used for the export.
* export_debug (bool, Default: false): Whether to export with debug symbols.
* export_encrypt_files (bool, Default: false): Whether to encrypt the exported files.
* export_executable (String, Default: ""): The name of the executable file.
* export_icon (Texture2D, Default: null): The icon for the application.
* export_icon_large (Texture2D, Default: null): A larger version of the icon for the application.
* export_path (String, Default: ""): The path where the export will be saved.
* export_permissions (String, Default: ""): Permissions for the exported files.
* export_runnable_path (String, Default: ""): Path to the runnable executable.
* export_runnable_args (String, Default: ""): Arguments to pass to the runnable executable.
* export_shading_language (int, Default: 0): The shading language to use for the export.
* export_signature (String, Default: ""): Signature for the exported files.
* export_texture_filter (int, Default: 0): The texture filter to use for the export.
* export_texture_format (int, Default: 0): The texture format to use for the export.
* export_vram_compressed (bool, Default: false): Whether to use VRAM compression for textures.
* export_vram_compressed_quality (int, Default: 0): The quality setting for VRAM compression.

Methods:
* get_name() → String: Returns the name of the export platform.
* get_os_name() → String: Returns the operating system name.
* get_supported_architectures() → Array[int]: Returns the supported CPU architectures.
* get_supported_renderers() → Array[int]: Returns the supported renderers.
* get_texture_formats() → Array[int]: Returns the supported texture formats.
* get_vram_compressed_formats() → Array[int]: Returns the supported VRAM compressed formats.
* get_vram_compressed_quality() → Array[int]: Returns the supported VRAM compressed quality settings.
* get_vram_compressed_quality_name(quality: int) → String: Returns the name of a VRAM compressed quality setting.
* get_vram_compressed_quality_value(name: String) → int: Returns the value of a VRAM compressed quality setting by name.
* get_vram_compressed_texture_format(format: int) → int: Returns the VRAM compressed texture format for a given format.
* get_vram_compressed_texture_format_name(format: int) → String: Returns the name of a VRAM compressed texture format.
* get_vram_compressed_texture_format_value(name: String) → int: Returns the value of a VRAM compressed texture format by name.
* get_vram_compressed_texture_format_with_quality(format: int, quality: int) → int: Returns the VRAM compressed texture format with a specific quality setting.
* get_vram_compressed_texture_format_with_quality_name(format: int, quality: int) → String: Returns the name of a VRAM compressed texture format with a specific quality setting.
* get_vram_compressed_texture_format_with_quality_value(format: int, quality: int) → int: Returns the value of a VRAM compressed texture format with a specific quality setting.
* get_vram_compressed_texture_format_with_quality_value_name(format: int, quality: int) → String: Returns the name of a VRAM compressed texture format with a specific quality setting.
* get_vram_compressed_texture_format_with_quality_value_with_name(format: int, quality: int, name: String) → int: Returns the value of a VRAM compressed texture format with a specific quality setting and name.
* get_vram_compressed_texture_format_with_quality_value_with_name_and_quality(format: int, quality: int, name: String) → int: Returns the value of a VRAM compressed texture format with a specific quality setting and name.
* get_vram_compressed_texture_format_with_quality_value_with_name_and_quality_and_format(format: int, quality: int, name: String, format_value: int) → int: Returns the value of a VRAM compressed texture format with a specific quality setting, name, and format value.
