Document: EditorExportPlatformLinuxBSD
Path: godot/classes/class_editorexportplatformlinuxbsd.rst
Summary: Provides export functionality for Linux and BSD platforms within the Godot editor.

Inherits: EditorExportPlatformPC < EditorExportPlatform < RefCounted < Object

This class handles the export process for Linux and BSD operating systems. It allows users to configure and build projects for these platforms directly from the Godot editor.
---CHUNK---
Document: EditorExportPlatformLinuxBSD
Path: godot/classes/class_editorexportplatformlinuxbsd.rst
Summary: This document describes the EditorExportPlatformLinuxBSD class, which handles exporting projects for Linux and BSD platforms.

Inherits: EditorExportPlatform < RefCounted

This class is used for exporting projects to Linux and BSD platforms. It provides methods and properties specific to the Linux/BSD export process.

Methods:
get_name() → StringName
Returns the name of the export platform.

get_os_name() → StringName
Returns the OS name associated with this export platform.

get_package_name() → StringName
Returns the default package name for the export.

get_export_options() → Array[Dictionary]
Returns an array of dictionaries, where each dictionary defines an export option. These options allow users to configure specific settings for the export process.

get_preset_file_extensions() → PackedStringArray
Returns an array of file extensions for preset files.

get_template_file_extension() → String
Returns the file extension for the export template.

get_supported_architectures() → PackedStringArray
Returns an array of supported CPU architectures for the export platform.

get_windows_driver_options() → Array[Dictionary]
Returns an array of dictionaries defining options related to Windows drivers, though this might be a legacy or mislabeled option as the class is for Linux/BSD.

get_linux_driver_options() → Array[Dictionary]
Returns an array of dictionaries defining options related to Linux drivers.

get_bsd_driver_options() → Array[Dictionary]
Returns an array of dictionaries defining options related to BSD drivers.

get_linux_icon_path() → String
Returns the path to the default icon for Linux exports.

get_bsd_icon_path() → String
Returns the path to the default icon for BSD exports.

get_linux_executable_path() → String
Returns the path to the default executable for Linux exports.

get_bsd_executable_path() → String
Returns the path to the default executable for BSD exports.

