Document: EditorExportPlatformLinuxBSD
Path: godot/classes/class_editorexportplatformlinuxbsd.rst
Summary: Properties for configuring Linux/BSD export options.

Properties:
* binary_format/architecture (String): Specifies the binary format architecture.
* binary_format/embed_pck (bool): Embeds the PCK file into the executable.
* custom_template/debug (String): Path to a custom debug export template.
* custom_template/release (String): Path to a custom release export template.
* debug/export_console_wrapper (int): Configures the console wrapper for debugging.
* shader_baker/enabled (bool): Enables or disables the shader baker.
* ssh_remote_deploy/cleanup_script (String): Path to a script for cleaning up remote deployments via SSH.
* ssh_remote_deploy/enabled (bool): Enables or disables remote deployment via SSH.
* ssh_remote_deploy/extra_args_scp (String): Extra arguments for SCP when deploying via SSH.
* ssh_remote_deploy/extra_args_ssh (String): Extra arguments for SSH when deploying via SSH.
* ssh_remote_deploy/host (String): The hostname or IP address for SSH remote deployment.
* ssh_remote_deploy/port (String): The port number for SSH remote deployment.
* ssh_remote_deploy/run_script (String): Path to a script to run on the remote host after deployment via SSH.
* texture_format/etc2_astc (bool): Enables ETC2/ASTC texture compression.
* texture_format/s3tc_bptc (bool): Enables S3TC/BPTC texture compression.
---CHUNK---
Document: EditorExportPlatformLinuxBSD
Path: godot/classes/class_editorexportplatformlinuxbsd.rst
Summary: Describes the properties available for configuring Linux/BSD exports in Godot Engine.

Property Descriptions
binary_format/architecture (String): Application executable architecture. Supported architectures: x86_32, x86_64, arm64, arm32, rv64, ppc64, and loongarch64. Official export templates include x86_32, x86_64, arm32, and arm64 binaries only.
binary_format/embed_pck (bool): If true, project resources are embedded into the executable.
custom_template/debug (String): Path to the custom export template. If left empty, default template is used.
custom_template/release (String): Path to the custom export template. If left empty, default template is used.
debug/export_console_wrapper (int): If true, a console wrapper is exported alongside the main executable, which allows running the project with enabled console output.
shader_baker/enabled (bool): If true, shaders will be compiled and embedded in the application. This option is only supported when using the Forward+ or Mobile renderers. Note: When exporting as a dedicated server, the shader baker is always disabled since no rendering is performed.
ssh_remote_deploy/cleanup_script (String): Script code to execute on the remote host when app is finished. The following variables can be used in the script: {temp_dir} - Path of temporary folder on the remote, used to upload app and scripts to. {archive_name} - Name of the ZIP containing uploaded application. {exe_name} - Name of application executable. {cmd_args} - Array of the command line argument for the application.
ssh_remote_deploy/enabled (bool): Enables remote deploy using SSH/SCP.
ssh_remote_deploy/extra_args_scp (String): Array of the additional command line arguments passed to the SCP.
ssh_remote_deploy/extra_args_ssh (String): Array of the additional command line arguments passed to the SSH.
ssh_remote_deploy/host (String): Remote host SSH user name and address, in user@address format.
ssh_remote_deploy/port (String): Remote host SSH port number.
ssh_remote_deploy/run_script (String): Script code to execute on the remote host when running the app. The following variables can be used in the script: {temp_dir} - Path of temporary folder on the remote, used to upload app and scripts to. {archive_name} - Name of the ZIP containing uploaded application. {exe_name} - Name of application executable. {cmd_args} - Array of the command line argument for the application.
texture_format/etc2_astc (bool): If true, project textures are exported in the ETC2/ASTC format.
texture_format/s3tc_bptc (bool): If true, project textures are exported in the S3TC/BPTC format.